<p><em>Secure Pipes</em> manages SSH port forwardings, so itâ€™s not neccessary to open up a SSH connection in the terminal to create a local or remote port forwarding. [<a href="https://www.opoet.com/pyro/">https://www.opoet.com/pyro/</a>]</p>

<h2 id="spectacle">Spectacle</h2>
<p><em>Spectacle</em> is a small little tool, which performs a task very well which macOS for some reason doesnâ€™t offer: managing window layouts with simple keystrokes. [<a href="https://www.spectacleapp.com">https://www.spectacleapp.com</a>]</p>

<h2 id="caffeine">Caffeine</h2>
