<h2 id="appcleaner">AppCleaner</h2>
<p><em>AppCleaner</em> removes macOS applications from disk completely, including all settings and related file clutter. [<a href="https://freemacsoft.net/appcleaner/">https://freemacsoft.net/appcleaner/</a>]</p>

<h2 id="realvnc-viewer">RealVNC Viewer</h2>
<p>Although macOS has an integrated VNC client, <em>RealVNC viewer</em> is the better choice in most cases. [<a href="https://www.realvnc.com/en/connect/download/viewer/">https://www.realvnc.com/en/connect/download/viewer/</a>]</p>

<h2 id="vlc">VLC</h2>
<p>Pure and simple, <em>VLC</em> is the best mediaplayer ever. Although the UI is not the nicest, itâ€™s simple and perforce well. [<a href="https://www.videolan.org/vlc/index.de.html">https://www.videolan.org/vlc/index.de.html</a>]</p>

<h2 id="the-unarchiver">The Unarchiver</h2>
<p><em>The Unarchiver</em> is more feature-rich than the build-in macOS archiving app. [<a href="https://theunarchiver.com">https://theunarchiver.com</a>]</p>

<h2 id="cyberduck">Cyberduck</h2>
<p><em>Cyberduck</em> is a clean and simple file-transfer tool. It supports FTP, SFTP, Amazon S3 and many more. [<a href="https://cyberduck.io">https://cyberduck.io</a>]</p>

<h2 id="microsoft-remote-desktop">Microsoft Remote Desktop</h2>
